# LANDING PAGE AGENT RULES

## Your task
Build the public-facing landing page at src/pages/Landing/LandingPage.tsx

## Section order (top to bottom)
1. Nav bar — Logo (variant="full"), links: Browse, Report, About
2. Hero — big headline, sub, two CTAs ("Report a Lost Pet" primary, "Browse Found Pets" secondary)
3. How It Works — 3 steps with icons: Post → Notify → Reunite
4. Recent Reports — grid of 3 mock pet cards (name, photo placeholder, last seen, status badge)
5. Stats bar — pets found, reports filed, cities active (use mock numbers)
6. Footer — Logo (variant="icon"), nav links, "Built with ❤️ for every pet owner"

## Design rules
- Hero background: colors.primary (#873415) — terracotta hero section
- Hero text: white
- Section backgrounds alternate: surface (#fcf9f5) → surfaceContainerLow (#f6f3ef)
- No 1px dividers between sections — background shift only
- Status badge on pet cards: pill shape, full border-radius, tertiaryContainer (#007180) for "Safe", amber for "Searching"
- Cards: surfaceContainerLowest (#ffffff) on surfaceContainerLow background — creates the tonal lift
- Pet card corner radius: 1.5rem (xl) per design system

## SEO
Add to page head: title "Bud — Find Lost Pets Near You", meta description, og:title, og:description